OL,3,GWest Midlands
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FGenerally
OL,6,Fdry this evening with clear spells.
OL,7,FStaying mainly dry overnight but
OL,8,Fturning rather windy through the early
OL,9,Fhours, with a chance of gales over the
OL,10,FPeak District by dawn. A few showery
OL,11,Foutbreaks possible later. Staying mild
OL,12,Fand frost-free.
OL,13,
OL,14,CThursday:FMainly dry through the
OL,15,Fmorning, but occasional rain
OL,16,Fdeveloping by lunchtime, turning
OL,17,Fheavier and more persistent through
OL,18,Fthe afternoon. Mild but windy with
OL,19,Fwinds touching gale force in places.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
